title: @OspreyMTEN's Zuern Victorious Twice on Sunday at Saint Francis Health System ITA All-American Championships
text: , who is at the tournament. "He did not play his best tennis, but he found a way to win and that's what two good tennis players do. To win 7-6 in the third set in two consecutive matches is huge." To start the day, Zuern battled back to edge out Buffalos's Amar Hromic 6-7 (5), 6-1, 7-6 (4) in the Round of 128. He followed that up with a 6-3, 3-6, 7-6 (3) Round of 64 triumph over Middle Tennessee's Gian Issa, who was ranked No. 9-16 in the Pre-Qualifying round. Zuern faces Julian Childers from Illinois on Monday at 9 a.m. EST/8 a.m. CST, with a chance to advance to the Qualifying Singles round on the line.
